The AMAA-StarTimes Short Film Festival (The Shorts) has had an amazing number of submissions for its maiden edition with over five hundred shorts submitted from across Africa and African Diaspora. The Shorts is currently at the screening stage as the selection committee led by the Chairman of the Africa Movie Academy Awards Screening Committee, Shaibu Husseini, is getting the selections ready. 		 			EmmCee RNB releases new single ahead of debut project		 		 		 			JT hopes new EP Love & Afrobeat will preach love		 		 		 			GUS 12 winner Odudu explains reasons for supporting widows		 		 Two hundred short films will be selected and shown from April 25 to May, 25, which is Africa Day on the ST Nollywood Plus channel and StarTimes-ON mobile app. The sum of $6000, a laptop and two phones are up for grabs.